sols_latex:
Newton's method is defined by $x_{n+1} = x_n - \frac{f(x_n)}{f'(x_n)}$,
where $x_n$ is the $n$-th approximation to a root of $f$.

We are given that $x_1 = -1~$. Applying the equation above,\\\\
\begin{align*}
x_{1+1} &= x_1 - \frac{f(x_1)}{f'(x_1)}
\\ x_2 &= -1 - \frac{f(-1)}{f'(-1)}
\\ &= -1 - \frac{(-1)^7 + 4}{7(-1)^6}
\\ &= -1 - \frac{-1 + 4}{7\cdot1}
\\ &= {\color{blue} -\frac{10}{7}}
\end{align*}

