We are given that &lt;math>x_1 = -1~&lt;/math>. Applying the equation above,&lt;br>&lt;br>

&lt;math>
\begin{align}
x_{1+1} &amp;= x_1 - \frac{f(x_1)}{f'(x_1)}
\\ x_2 &amp;= -1 - \frac{f(-1)}{f'(-1)}
\\ &amp;= -1 - \frac{(-1)^7 + 4}{7(-1)^6}
\\ &amp;= -1 - \frac{-1 + 4}{7\cdot1}
\\ &amp;= {\color{blue} -\frac{10}{7}}
\end{align}
&lt;/math>
